[The meaning of "higher titres of Coxsackie B4 virus" and "parvovirus 19
was also found negative in some of the sera tested" are not clear. No
information provided as to signs and symptoms in the adult patients. I am
assuming that virus isolation assays were done and that is what was meant
by "high titre". Can't fulfill Koch's postulates, as always, but if the
coxsackie B4 titers were high and the parvovirus tests negative, what is
the diagnostic question. Looks like a coxsackie B4 outbreak to me. -
Mod.CHC
